Quoting James Jackson <firesong4ng(-at-)hotmail.com>:
> Can I use a standard 4 wire trailer kit?

Nope. You need an adapter to integrate the amber turn signals with the brake
lights. Canadian Tiren and Napa both carry these for around $20.


> Anything funny I need to think about while
> wiring it up?

Nope. Unless you want to consider creating a trailer with amber turn 
signals. I
did that with the westrailer. The voltage for the amber lights is supplied
using a 2-terminal connector in addition to the standard 4-wire setup.

> Wheres the easiest point to tap into the
> wiring.. at one of the rear lights?

That's how I did it.

Happy Trails,

